Clean Data

std<-read_dta("C:\\Users\\faris\\OneDrive\\Documents\\ECON\\Applied Data\\Midterm\\PISAIDNSTDQQ.dta")
std <- std[, c(grep("^(PV\\d+MATH|PV\\d+READ|PV\\d+SCIE)", names(std), value = TRUE), "CNTSCHID","ESCS","ST004D01T","MATHPERS","ISCEDP","TEACHSUP","ST272Q01JA","COGACMCO", "COGACRCO","LANGN"), with = FALSE]

std <- std %>%
  mutate(Read = rowMeans(select(., starts_with("PV") & ends_with("READ")), na.rm = TRUE)) %>%
  mutate(Math = rowMeans(select(., starts_with("PV") & ends_with("MATH")), na.rm = TRUE)) %>%
  mutate(Science = rowMeans(select(., starts_with("PV") & ends_with("SCIE")), na.rm = TRUE)) %>%
  rename(Female=ST004D01T,Math_Effort=MATHPERS,Foster_Reasoning=COGACRCO,Encourage_Thinking=COGACMCO,SES=ESCS)%>%
  select(-matches("^PV\\d+READ"),-matches("^PV\\d+MATH"),-matches("^PV\\d+SCIE"))%>%
  mutate(School_Type = case_when(
    ISCEDP == 244 ~ "Junior High School",
    ISCEDP == 344 ~ "Academic Senior High School",
    ISCEDP == 354 ~ "Vocational Senior High School",
    TRUE ~ as.character(ISCEDP)  # Keep other values unchanged
  ))%>%
  mutate(Indo_Language = case_when(
    LANGN == 113 ~ 1,
    LANGN == 313 | 642 | 823 | 999 ~ 0,
  ))%>%
  mutate(Female = case_when(
    Female == 1 ~ 1,
    Female == 2 ~ 0
  ))

sch<-read_dta("C:\\Users\\faris\\OneDrive\\Documents\\ECON\\Applied Data\\Midterm\\PISAIDNSCHQQ.dta")
sch <- sch[, c("CNTSCHID","PRIVATESCH","STDTEST","TDTEST","SC034Q01NA","SC195Q03JA")]
sch<-sch %>%
  mutate(Private=ifelse(PRIVATESCH=="private",1,0))%>%
  rename(Usage_StdTest=STDTEST,Usage_TeacherTest=TDTEST,TeacherTest_Freq=SC195Q03JA,StdTest_Freq=SC034Q01NA)

merged_pisa <- merge(std, sch, by = "CNTSCHID", all = FALSE)
merged_pisa <- na.omit(merged_pisa)

#merged_pisa <- merged_pisa[sample(nrow(merged_pisa), size = 500), ]

main_data <- merged_pisa %>%
  select(Math,Read,Science, Math_Effort,TeacherTest_Freq,StdTest_Freq,SES,Encourage_Thinking,Foster_Reasoning,Usage_StdTest,Usage_TeacherTest)

desc_table<-merged_pisa %>%
  select(Math,Read,Science, Math_Effort,TeacherTest_Freq,StdTest_Freq,SES,Encourage_Thinking,Foster_Reasoning,Usage_StdTest,Usage_TeacherTest,SES, Private, Female,School_Type,Indo_Language)

main_data<-scale(main_data)

ses_data<- merged_pisa %>%
  select(SES)

private_data<- merged_pisa %>%
  select(Private)

female_data<- merged_pisa %>%
  select(Female)

ISCEDP_data<- merged_pisa %>%
  select(School_Type)

language<- merged_pisa %>%
  select(Indo_Language)

Figure 1 Heatmap

m<-main_data

uncenter.dist<-function(m) {
  as.dist(as.matrix(distancematrix(m, d="cosangle")))
}

row.clus<-hclust(uncenter.dist(m), method = "ave")
col.clus<-hclust(uncenter.dist(t(m)), method = "ave")

main<-Heatmap(m,name="PISA", cluster_rows=row.clus, cluster_columns=col.clus,column_names_rot = 55,show_row_names = FALSE,top_annotation=HeatmapAnnotation(Density=anno_density(m, joyplot_scale=2,gp = gpar(fill = "#CCCCCC80"),height=unit(2,"cm"))))
## `use_raster` is automatically set to TRUE for a matrix with more than
## 2000 rows. You can control `use_raster` argument by explicitly setting
## TRUE/FALSE to it.
## 
## Set `ht_opt$message = FALSE` to turn off this message.
## 'magick' package is suggested to install to give better rasterization.
## 
## Set `ht_opt$message = FALSE` to turn off this message.
anno1<-Heatmap(private_data,name="Private",col=c("black","white"),heatmap_legend_param = list(at = c(0,1),labels = c("Public", "Private")),show_row_names = FALSE,column_names_rot = 55)
## Warning: The input is a data frame-like object, convert it to a matrix.
female_data$Female <- factor(female_data$Female, levels = c(0, 1), labels = c("Male","Female"))

anno2<-Heatmap(female_data,name="Female",show_row_names = FALSE,column_names_rot = 55)
## Warning: The input is a data frame-like object, convert it to a matrix.
## Warning: Note: not all columns in the data frame are numeric. The data frame
## will be converted into a character matrix.
anno3<-Heatmap(ISCEDP_data,name="School",col=c("#1E88E5","#FFC107","#D81B60"),show_row_names = FALSE,column_names_rot = 55)
## Warning: The input is a data frame-like object, convert it to a matrix.
## Warning: Note: not all columns in the data frame are numeric. The data frame
## will be converted into a character matrix.
anno4<-Heatmap(language,name="Language",col=c("black","white"),heatmap_legend_param = list(at = c(0,1),labels = c("Non Indonesian", "Indonesian")),show_row_names = FALSE,column_names_rot = 55)
## Warning: The input is a data frame-like object, convert it to a matrix.
draw(main+anno1+anno2+anno3+anno4)

pdf("C:\\Users\\faris\\OneDrive\\Documents\\ECON\\Applied Data\\Midterm\\heatmap.pdf",width=8, height=10)

ggplot(merged_pisa, aes(x = factor(StdTest_Freq), y = Math, colour = School_Type, fill = School_Type)) +
  stat_summary(fun = "mean", geom = "point", size = 3, position = position_dodge(width = 0.8), alpha = 0.4) +  # Dodging points
  stat_summary(fun.data = "mean_cl_normal", geom = "errorbar", width = 0.2, position = position_dodge(width = 0.8), alpha = 0.75) +  # Dodging error bars
  geom_smooth(aes(group = School_Type), method = "gam", formula = y ~ poly(x, 3), se = F, size = 1.5) +  # Add smooth line for each school type
  labs(x = "Testing Frequency", y = "Math Score") +
  theme_minimal() +
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 0, hjust = 1),
        panel.grid.major = element_blank(),  # Remove major grid lines
        panel.grid.minor = element_blank(),  # Remove minor grid lines
        legend.position = "none",# Remove legend
        plot.title = element_text(size = 16, hjust = 0.5)) +  
  scale_x_discrete(labels = c("1" = "0", "2" = "1 - 2", "3" = "3 - 5", "4" = "12", "5" = ">12")) +  # Change x-axis labels
  labs(
    title = "More Standardized Testing, Lower Scores",
    x = "Standardized Testing Frequency",
    y = "Math Scores")+  # Add annotations with specified colors
  annotate("text", x = 3.5, y = 415, label = "Academic Senior High School", size = 3.5, colour = "#F8766D", hjust = 0,fontface = "bold") +  # Annotation for Academic (Color #F8766D)

Figure 4 and 5

# Reshape data to long format
merged_pisa_long <- merged_pisa %>%
  pivot_longer(cols = c(Encourage_Thinking, Foster_Reasoning, Math_Effort),
               names_to = "Measure",  # New column for the variable names
               values_to = "Score")   # New column for the values

ggplot(merged_pisa_long, aes(x = factor(StdTest_Freq), y = Score, group=interaction(Private,StdTest_Freq), fill = Private)) +
  geom_boxplot() +
  facet_wrap(~Measure, scales = "free_y") +  # Create a separate plot for each measure
  theme_minimal() +
  theme(
    panel.grid.major = element_blank(),
    panel.grid.minor = element_blank(),
    axis.text.x = element_text(size = 10, angle = 0, hjust = 0.5),
    axis.title.x = element_text(size = 14),
    axis.title.y = element_text(size = 14),
    plot.title = element_text(size = 16, hjust = 0.5)
  ) +
  labs(
    title = "Standardized Tests Don’t Drive Student Effort or Instruction Quality", 
    x = "Frequency of Standardized Test in a Year", 
    y = "Score"
  )+
  scale_x_discrete(labels = c("0", "1 - 2", "3 - 5", "12", ">12"))
